As with all viruses, SARS-COV-2, the virus that causes COVID-19, will continue to evolve as long as it continues to spread. The more that the virus spreads, the more pressure there is for the virus to change. So, the best way to prevent more variants from emerging is to stop the spread of the virus. To protect yourself and others from COVID-19:Keep a distance of at least 1 metre from othersWear a well-fitted mask over your mouth and noseOpen windows Cough or sneeze into a bent elbow or tissueClean your hands frequentlyGet vaccinated as soon as it is your turn 
